scopecontent.head: COLLECTION DESCRIPTION
scopecontent.p: Correspondence, photographs, clippings, and biographical data concerning Cornell University alumni.

descgrp.head: INFORMATION FOR USERS
descgrp.p: To place a request, ask for staff assistance. Provide alumnus's/alumna's name, and death date if known.

The dates listed in the container list below are the alumni's/alumnae's death dates. The date is sometimes the date the file was pulled and may not correspond exactly to the date of death. For staff, retrieving box numbers from the alumni database is advised, or checking adjacent years if a folder is not found.

accessrestrict.head: Access Restrictions:
accessrestrict.p: Living alumni files are stored separately. Only records of deceased alumni are open for research.

prefercite.head: Cite As:
prefercite.p: Deceased Alumni files, #41-2-877. Division of Rare and Manuscript Collections, Cornell University Library.

relatedmaterial.head: RELATED MATERIALS
relatedmaterial.p: For alumni killed during World War Two see World War II servicemen alumni files, 1939-1945, #41-2-822.

scopecontent.p: For alumni deceased during this period box numbers can be retrieved upon request.
